<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Ammonia Information</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2F4F4F;
            --primary-light: #3a5f5f;
            --secondary: #778899;
            --accent: #20B2AA;
            --light-bg: #f5f5f5;
            --dark-text: #2d3748;
            --border-color: #e0e0e0;
            --white: #ffffff;
            --dark-bg: #1e1e1e;
            --dark-card: #2b2b2b;
            --dark-text-color: #dddddd;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--light-bg);
            transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
        }

        body.dark-mode {
            background-color: var(--dark-bg);
            color: var(--dark-text-color);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            background: var(--white);
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .dark-mode .container {
            background: var(--dark-card);
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .dark-mode h1 {
            color: var(--accent);
            border-bottom-color: var(--primary-light);
        }

        p {
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: var(--dark-text);
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .dark-mode p {
            color: var(--dark-text-color);
        }

        .responsive-img {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .responsive-img:hover {
            transform: scale(1.02);
        }

        button {
            display: block;
            margin: 25px auto;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        .dark-mode button {
            background-color: var(--accent);
        }

        .dark-mode button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
        }

        .hidden {
            display: none;
        }

        .chemical-formula {
            font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
            font-style: italic;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--accent);
        }

        .dark-mode .chemical-formula {
            color: var(--primary-light);
        }

        /* Back button */
        .back-button-container {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        .dark-mode .back-button {
            background-color: var(--accent);
        }

        .dark-mode .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
        }

        /* Theme toggle */
        #themeToggle {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            right: 20px;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            background: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background 0.3s;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        #themeToggle:hover {
            background: var(--primary-light);
        }

        

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                margin: 15px;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
            
            .back-button-container {
                position: relative;
                top: auto;
                left: auto;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Back to Home Button -->
    <div class="back-button-container">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBackHome()">&#8592; Back to Parameters</button>
    </div>

   

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Ammonia & Ammonium in Water</h1>
        <p>
            <span class="chemical-formula">Ammonium (NH<sub>4</sub><sup>+</sup>)</span> or its uncharged form <span class="chemical-formula">ammonia (NH<sub>3</sub>)</span> is a form of nitrogen which
            aquatic plants can absorb and incorporate into proteins, amino acids, and other molecules.
        </p>
        <p>
            High concentrations of ammonium can enhance the growth of algae and aquatic plants.
            Bacteria can also convert high ammonium to <span class="chemical-formula">nitrate (NO<sub>3</sub><sup>-</sup>)</span> in the process of nitrification,
            which lowers dissolved oxygen.
        </p>
        <img src="images/ammonia.png" alt="Ammonia Sensor" class="responsive-img">
        <p>
            Ammonia in water is either un-ionized ammonia or the ammonium ion. Typically, the value
            reported is the sum of both forms and is reported as total ammonia or simply ammonia.
            The relative proportion of the two forms present in water is highly affected by pH.
        </p>
        <button id="toggleInfo">Show More Information</button>
        <div id="extraInfo" class="hidden">
            <p>
                <strong>Un-ionized ammonia</strong> is the toxic form and predominates when pH is high. The <span class="chemical-formula">NH<sub>4</sub><sup>+</sup></span> ion is
                relatively non-toxic and predominates when pH is low.
            </p>
            <p>
                The equilibrium between <span class="chemical-formula">NH<sub>3</sub></span> and <span class="chemical-formula">NH<sub>4</sub><sup>+</sup></span> is also affected by temperature. More toxic ammonia is present in
                warmer water than in cooler water.
            </p>
            <p>
                Regular monitoring of ammonia levels is crucial in aquaculture, wastewater treatment, and environmental studies
                to prevent toxic conditions for aquatic life.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        function goBackHome() {
            window.location.href = 'parameters';
        }

        document.getElementById("toggleInfo").addEventListener("click", function() {
            const extraInfo = document.getElementById("extraInfo");
            const button = document.getElementById("toggleInfo");
            
            if (extraInfo.classList.contains("hidden")) {
                extraInfo.classList.remove("hidden");
                button.textContent = "Show Less Information";
            } else {
                extraInfo.classList.add("hidden");
                button.textContent = "Show More Information";
            }
        });

       
    </script>
</body>
</html>